<p class=caption>
Getting Started and Personalizing
</p><p>
These instructions explain some basic features and
let you personalize Magic Cap. The setup information
you enter here will be saved so you can use it later.
</p><p>
Click on the page corner above to turn the page.
</p></td></tr>

<tr><td colspan=2><br><table width=100% cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td width=50% height=8 style='background: url(intr/divleftfill.png)'><img width=1 height=8 src='intr/divleftfill.png'></td><td width=8 height=8><img width=8 height=8 src='intr/divmed.png'></td><td width=50% height=8 style='background: url(intr/divrightfill.png)'><img width=1 height=8 src='intr/divrightfill.png'></td></tr></table><br></td></tr>

<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/06.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p class=caption>
How to use this book
</p><p>
This book helps you set up and learn about Magic Cap
in a series of step-by-step lessons.
</p><p>
Click &lsquo;start lesson&rsquo; to learn how the lessons work.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/07.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 1 of 6</b>
</p><p>
Lessons proceed step by step. Each step has a box
containing an explanation, just like this one.
</p><p>
Any information you supply in these lessons will
be kept and used by Magic Cap.
</p><p>
Click &lsquo;next&rsquo; to continue.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/08.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 2 of 6</b>
</p><p>
Some steps will point to the object you should click
next. For example, click the lips image now.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/09.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 3 of 6</b>
</p><p>
You can stop a lesson at any time by clicking the
&lsquo;stop&rsquo; button. You will have the opportunity to change
your mind. Try clicking &lsquo;stop&rsquo; now.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/10.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 4 of 6</b>
</p><p>
If you decide not to stop the lesson, click &lsquo;go on&rsquo;.
Click &lsquo;go on&rsquo; now.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/11.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 5 of 6</b>
</p><p>
Sometimes it is possible to get out of step with
the instructions. If this happens, clicking the
&lsquo;stop&rsquo; button lets you leave the lesson.
</p><p>
Click &lsquo;next&rsquo; to continue.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/12.png'></td></tr></table>
</td><td valign=top style='padding-bottom: 3em;'>
<p>
<b>Using this book &middot; step 6 of 6</b>
</p><p>
After you have completed a lesson, you can continue
to the next one by clicking on the right-hand page
corner. Or you can repeat the lesson.
</p><p>
That&rsquo;s the end of the lesson for this page. Click
&lsquo;done&rsquo; below.
</p></td></tr>
<tr><td valign=top align=center>
<table width=1 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 align=left class=screenshotmarginleft><tr><td align=left><img class=screenshot width=480 height=320 src='pics/tutorials/magiccap/13.png'></td></tr></table>
